  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>The L‐shaped region formed by three congruent squares is subdivided into four smaller L shapes in a fixed way. This subdivision is then carried out on each L shape, and the process is repeated a total of 2005 times (so that there are 4^(2005) L shapes at the end). How many of these L shapes have the same orientation as the original one?</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "We are told that the subdivision produces four L shapes from one L shape and that the arrangement is fixed, independent of the parent’s orientation. In other words, every time an L is subdivided the four daughter L’s always occur in the same four fixed orientations with respect to the overall (global) frame. In particular, exactly one of the four daughter L’s appears in the same orientation as the original L shape. Thus, from every L shape (no matter its own orientation) the subdivision produces exactly one copy (in the four new pieces) that has the original orientation. Starting with one original L, after one subdivision there is exactly 1 L in the original orientation among 4 pieces. In the next subdivision every one of the 4 pieces produces exactly one daughter in the original orientation so that the total number in that generation is 4. In general, at each subdivision the number of original‐oriented L’s is multiplied by 4^(n) from the previous generation’s count of L’s in any orientation? Not quite – the important fact is that every one of the L’s present (all 4^(k) L’s at stage k) produces exactly one L in the original orientation in the next stage. Therefore, if we let a_n be the number of L’s in the original orientation after n subdivisions, then a_(n+1) = (number of L’s at stage n)×(1 per L) = 4^n. Since at stage 1 we have a_1 = 1 (because from the single original L we get one L in the original orientation), it follows that at stage 2 there will be 4^1 = 4, at stage 3 there will be 4^2, and generally after n subdivisions the number is 4^(n-1). Here n = 2005. Therefore, the number of L’s that are in the same orientation as the original after 2005 subdivisions is 4^(2005 - 1) = 4^(2004).",
  "final_answer": "<answer>4^(2004)</answer>"
}

