  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>How many two-digit prime numbers have the property that both of their digits are prime numbers?</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "1. Identify the prime digits: 2, 3, 5, and 7. 
2. List all two-digit numbers where both the tens and units digits are chosen from {2, 3, 5, 7}. These numbers include: 22, 23, 25, 27, 32, 33, 35, 37, 52, 53, 55, 57, 72, 73, 75, 77. 
