}\\) grows polynomially (like \\(n^{463}\\)) but is multiplied by \\(S(N)\\) which decays exponentially fast, the overall numerator is asymptotically 0. Dividing by \\(KB\\log\\log n\\) (with \\(KB\\) assumed to be a fixed constant) does not change the limit.\\n\\n7. Thus, the limit evaluates to 0.",
