  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Call a sequence of positive integers {aₙ} good if for any distinct positive integers m and n one has gcd(m, n) | aₘ² + aₙ² and gcd(aₘ, aₙ) | m² + n². Call a positive integer a to be k‐good if there exists a good sequence for which aₖ = a. Does there exist a positive integer k such that there are exactly 2019 k‐good positive integers?</denoised_question>",
