  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>If the mean (average) of 5 consecutive integers is 9, what is the smallest of these integers?</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "Let the smallest integer be n. Then the consecutive integers are n, n+1, n+2, n+3, and n+4. The mean of these integers is (n + (n+1) + (n+2) + (n+3) + (n+4)) / 5 = (5n + 10) / 5 = n + 2. We are given that this mean is 9, so setting up the equation n + 2 = 9, we solve for n by subtracting 2 from both sides and obtain n = 7.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>7</answer>"
